1
00:00:50,417 --> 00:00:54,607
-You're always sick.
-You were sick when you were my age.

2
00:00:58,158 --> 00:01:01,118
-Evening, sir.
-Evening, Victor.

3
00:01:02,296 --> 00:01:04,545
I didn't realize you were still here.

4
00:01:05,632 --> 00:01:08,912
I was just keeping James company, sir,
if that's all right.

5
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,668
Very kind of you.

6
00:01:14,107 --> 00:01:16,477
-Any better, Son?
-Still cold, Father.

7
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:18,551
Just a mild fever.

8
00:01:18,812 --> 00:01:21,622
-You'll be all right in the morning.
-You always say that.

9
00:01:22,115 --> 00:01:24,104
And you always pull through, don't you?

10
00:01:24,484 --> 00:01:27,473
-Yeah.
-Now, you taking your medicine?

11
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:32,090
Elizabeth! Elizabeth!

12
00:01:33,126 --> 00:01:35,086
-Your father's drunk again.
-Elizabeth!

13
00:01:35,462 --> 00:01:39,272
-You should help him home, Victor.
-It's not my name he's calling, sir.

14
00:01:41,368 --> 00:01:42,857
-Father!
-Stay where you are, James.

15
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:44,810
-Get off me!
-Father!

16
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:47,939
Now! You never loved him!

17
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:51,079
I told you never to come back here.

18
00:01:58,218 --> 00:01:59,418
Get out!

19
00:02:11,098 --> 00:02:12,468
James?

20
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:19,960
-No.
-James?

21
00:02:21,408 --> 00:02:23,047
-There are things you don't understand.
-Don't.

22
00:02:23,377 --> 00:02:24,777
-l need him to know!
-Please don't.

23
00:02:25,078 --> 00:02:26,778
-No more lies.
-James...

24
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,578
-No!
-James!

25
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:55,219
He... He wasn't your father,

26
00:03:03,984 --> 00:03:05,124
Son.

27
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,397
What are you?

28
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:33,581
-I didn't mean it! 1 didn't mean it!
-Yes, you did!

29
00:03:35,015 --> 00:03:37,644
He deserved it, and you gave it to him.

30
00:03:41,154 --> 00:03:43,524
We're brothers, Jimmy. You realize that?

31
00:03:44,491 --> 00:03:46,571
And brothers protect each other.

32
00:03:47,194 --> 00:03:50,474
You have to be hard now,
hard so nothing can ever touch us.

33
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:54,268
-l want to go home.
-We can't.

34
00:03:55,001 --> 00:03:56,961
We stick together, no matter what,

35
00:03:57,337 --> 00:04:00,087
and take care of anyone
who gets in our way.

36
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,744
Can you do that, little brother?

37
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,508
-I'm going down to the river.
-They're coming.

38
00:04:07,948 --> 00:04:10,408
-Head over the hill. Hurry!
-Can you run?

39
00:04:14,321 --> 00:04:18,130
-Keep on running and don't look back.
-Okay.

40
00:05:21,288 --> 00:05:22,548
Back to back!

41
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,290
That's enough!

42
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:25,164
Enough!

43
00:06:38,598 --> 00:06:39,908
No! No!

44
00:06:41,368 --> 00:06:42,948
Stand down, soldier!

45
00:06:48,975 --> 00:06:50,205
Victor!

46
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:54,772
Stand down! Stand down!

47
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:57,038
Stand down!

48
00:07:00,854 --> 00:07:01,873
No!

49
00:07:28,181 --> 00:07:30,700
Ready, aim...

50
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:33,235
Wake me when it's over.

51
00:07:42,963 --> 00:07:43,863
.. fire!

52
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:53,006
Freaks! You're animals! Freaks!

53
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:55,525
My name is Major William Stryker.

54
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:58,659
You've been charged
with killing a senior officer.

55
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,815
Is that correct?

56
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:03,017
Apparently, we have some issues
with authority...

57
00:08:03,383 --> 00:08:05,722
-Just keep a lid on it.
-
-...SIP.

58
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:09,647
The warden tells me that your sentence
was carried out by a firing squad

59
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:11,700
at 1000 hours.

60
00:08:12,025 --> 00:08:13,924
-How'd that go?
-It tickled.

61
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:23,069
You boys tired of running?
Tired of denying your true nature?

62
00:08:24,637 --> 00:08:26,747
-What do you care?
-Oh, I care.

63
00:08:27,874 --> 00:08:30,094
I care because I know how special you are.

64
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,969
How valuable.

65
00:08:36,082 --> 00:08:39,891
Look, you can stay here
locked up like freaks of nature,

66
00:08:41,587 --> 00:08:43,137
so
or you can join me.

67
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:47,590
I'm putting together a special team
with special privileges.

68
00:08:49,162 --> 00:08:52,942
Now, tell me, how would you like
to really serve your country?

69
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:08,497
You know, I love this weapon

70
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:10,025
more than any other thing
in the whole wide world.

71
00:09:10,316 --> 00:09:12,046
-Do you wanna know why?
-No.

72
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:14,516
It's memorable.

73
00:09:14,821 --> 00:09:16,661
Sure, it's a little bulky,
tough to get on a plane.

74
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:20,093
You whip out a couple of swords
at your ex-girlfriend's wedding,

75
00:09:20,627 --> 00:09:22,617
they will never, ever forget it.

76
00:09:22,996 --> 00:09:24,576
That's funny, Wade.

77
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:27,828
I think you confuse me
with someone who gives a shit.

78
00:09:28,334 --> 00:09:30,733
Right, it's probably not
as intimidating as having a gun

79
00:09:31,171 --> 00:09:34,571
or bone claws
or the fingernails of a bag lady.

80
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:46,610
-Manicure?
-Victor. Easy.

81
00:09:49,622 --> 00:09:52,021
Fred got a new tattoo. I'm concerned.

82
00:09:53,293 --> 00:09:55,903
Oh, Jesus, Fred,
you just met her last night.

83
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:58,779
-l love her.
-You love her after one night?

84
00:09:59,199 --> 00:10:00,598
She's a gymnast.

85
00:10:02,202 --> 00:10:03,842
Bradley, take her down.

86
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,517
Oh, God.

87
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:12,546
-Are you gonna puke?
-lf we were meant to fly,

88
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:14,429
-we'd grow wings.
-Don't worry, Nancy.

89
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:17,707
-More people die driving than flying.
-How about from impaling?

90
00:10:18,218 --> 00:10:20,938
Hey, be nice,
or be your approximation of nice.

91
00:10:22,856 --> 00:10:24,586
-Would you like a bucket?
-No.

92
00:10:24,924 --> 00:10:26,794
Gentlemen, wheels down in Lagos in five.

93
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:06,626
-Why are we here?
-All in good time. Zero?

94
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:16,379
-Intruder! Perimeter breach!
-Man the weapon!

95
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:21,958
Intruder, stop!
Put your hands behind your head!

96
00:11:52,011 --> 00:11:53,351
Having fun yet?

97
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:00,401
-Fred?
-The tank?

98
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,520
-The tank.
-Yeah, I got that.

99
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:42,765
Great. Stuck in an elevator
with five guys on a high-protein diet.

100
00:12:43,396 --> 00:12:44,976
-Wade.
-Dreams really do come true.

101
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:46,231
Just shut it!

102
00:12:46,466 --> 00:12:49,076
-You're up next.
-Thank you, sir. You look really nice today.

103
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:51,725
It's the green.
It brings out the seriousness in your eyes.

104
00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:55,598
-Oh, my God. Do you ever shut up, pal?
-No. Not when I'm awake.

105
00:12:56,976 --> 00:12:58,786
Bradley? Top floor, please.

106
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,710
Cover the elevator! The elevator!

107
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:21,479
Time to go to work.

108
00:13:58,371 --> 00:14:01,001
Okay. People are dead.

109
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:07,867
If you didn't have that mouth on you,
Wade, you'd be the perfect soldier.

110
00:14:13,453 --> 00:14:15,882
I wouldn't do that if 1 was you, brother.

111
00:14:20,259 --> 00:14:24,239
-Take the diamonds. They're yours.
-l don't want your diamonds.

112
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:27,429
I want this.

113
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:30,950
But that is nothing. A souvenir.

114
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:34,531
Where did you find it? l want the source.

115
00:14:35,908 --> 00:14:40,068
A small village, far inland,
three days from here.

116
00:14:43,182 --> 00:14:46,312
Tell him this rock is
more valuable to me than his life.

117
00:14:46,853 --> 00:14:48,632
Ask him where he found it.

118
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:00,925
Okay.

119
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:03,845
He says it came from the sky.

120
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:09,874
He's telling the truth.

121
00:15:10,977 --> 00:15:12,557
You don't know the language, Logan.

122
00:15:12,879 --> 00:15:14,719
-It's a meteor fragment.
-l know what it is.

123
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:17,161
I'm asking him where he found it.

124
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:19,740
Sir, base wants to know our location.

125
00:15:20,153 --> 00:15:22,113
-Shut them down.
-Yes.

126
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:26,571
Tell him everyone here will die

127
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,506
unless he tells me
where he found the rock.

128
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:42,348
-He says that it's sacred.
-Okay, fine.

129
00:15:46,479 --> 00:15:47,679
Victor.

130
00:16:04,897 --> 00:16:06,127
Victor!

131
00:16:09,936 --> 00:16:11,806
Don't even think about it.

132
00:16:13,506 --> 00:16:15,346
We didn't sign up for this.

133
00:16:19,212 --> 00:16:20,582
Put him down!

134
00:16:33,292 --> 00:16:34,842
What are you doing?

135
00:16:36,395 --> 00:16:38,564
We finally got a good thing going here.
Don't you screw this up.

136
00:16:38,965 --> 00:16:40,515
Enough. That's enough.
We've done enough.

137
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,642
Who do you think you are?

138
00:16:43,269 --> 00:16:44,759
This is what we do.

139
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:47,700
Maybe you'd rather be
rotting in a hole somewhere

140
00:16:48,074 --> 00:16:51,353
till they figure out a way to do it to us.
Is that it? Huh?

141
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:53,575
I'm done.

142
00:16:56,215 --> 00:16:57,475
You coming?

143
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:05,433
Jimmy!

144
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:13,143
We can't just let you walk away.

145
00:17:22,008 --> 00:17:23,028
Jimmy!

146
00:17:26,112 --> 00:17:27,222
Jimmy!

147
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:18,579
Why are you up so early?

148
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:22,667
Come here.

149
00:19:01,407 --> 00:19:02,776
See you, baby.

150
00:19:04,176 --> 00:19:05,285
Hey.

151
00:19:12,351 --> 00:19:14,721
Oh, that's nice. Yes. Take your time.

152
00:19:17,123 --> 00:19:18,083
You're wrapped, man.

153
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,665
Okay, I'm totally gonna get this.

154
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:42,963
Nope. Come on.

155
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,929
Oh, wow! Let's go on the Ferris wheel.

156
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,549
-How does he do it?
-Come on.

157
00:19:48,821 --> 00:19:50,221
..-amazing lady in a box!

158
00:19:59,565 --> 00:20:01,525
Swing the hammer, ring the bell!

159
00:20:01,901 --> 00:20:03,511
Hey, what do you do?

160
00:20:06,105 --> 00:20:08,035
If you turn off the light, you win a prize.

161
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:11,627
-Three tries for a buck.
-Come on, I wanna do it.

162
00:20:12,645 --> 00:20:14,195
There you go. Okay?

163
00:20:18,851 --> 00:20:20,371
No, that's obvious.

164
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:25,586
That's two.

165
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,333
Well, that's a stupid trick.

166
00:20:37,136 --> 00:20:38,776
It's not a trick, man.

167
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:41,245
Come on. Freak.

168
00:20:43,476 --> 00:20:44,526
Bye.

169
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:14,502
Show's over!

170
00:21:19,712 --> 00:21:21,932
I said show's over!

171
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:29,409
The show's never over for us, Bradley.

172
00:21:32,258 --> 00:21:34,598
-Victor.
-Aren't you gonna invite me in?

173
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:39,303
Yeah. Come on in.

174
00:21:52,378 --> 00:21:56,568
You know, I've never said anything
to anyone about what happened.

175
00:21:57,917 --> 00:22:00,107
I'm living a totally
different life now, Victor.

176
00:22:00,519 --> 00:22:02,479
No need to bring up the past.

177
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:19,200
You know,

178
00:22:20,539 --> 00:22:24,289
l always thought it would
be Wade to come knocking at my door.

179
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:28,010
Well... Well,

180
00:22:29,548 --> 00:22:30,778
Wade's gone.

181
00:22:34,486 --> 00:22:36,326
I'm not afraid of you, Victor.

182
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:41,088
I'm not afraid of dying.

183
00:22:42,595 --> 00:22:44,025
How do you know?

184
00:22:45,497 --> 00:22:47,427
You've never tried it before.

185
00:23:04,917 --> 00:23:06,557
Was it the wars?

186
00:23:08,287 --> 00:23:09,517
Which one?

187
00:23:10,256 --> 00:23:11,486
All of them.

188
00:23:19,598 --> 00:23:22,058
-Tell me.
-Hey.

189
00:23:23,269 --> 00:23:24,849
It's just a scratch.

190
00:23:32,444 --> 00:23:35,053
Looks like we're gonna need
new sheets again, baby.

191
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:36,744
Yeah.

192
00:24:01,707 --> 00:24:03,377
Who the hell is this?

193
00:24:03,709 --> 00:24:05,409
Smells like government.

194
00:24:09,882 --> 00:24:11,992
My God. Haven't aged a day!

195
00:24:12,384 --> 00:24:13,694
Clean living.

196
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:18,403
-You remember Agent Zero?
-Still shooting first, asking questions later?

197
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:24,189
-You still chewing on cheap cigars?
-Boys, please.

198
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:28,188
-l have a job for you.
-l already have a job.

199
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:30,407
Lumberjack? 18 grand a year?

200
00:24:30,769 --> 00:24:33,759
18.5. Plus I haven't had to kill anyone
in a while.

201
00:24:34,273 --> 00:24:36,003
-Starting to miss it?
-Right about now I am.

202
00:24:36,342 --> 00:24:38,332
-Yeah?
-Zero, back to the car.

203
00:24:42,214 --> 00:24:43,474
Attaboy.

204
00:24:50,255 --> 00:24:53,155
You know, I'm not proud about
the way things ended between us.

205
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:55,299
Conversation's over.

206
00:24:56,528 --> 00:24:59,688
Playing Little House on the Prairie
with a schoolteacher,

207
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:02,119
I mean, that just isn't you, Logan.

208
00:25:02,534 --> 00:25:04,284
And you would know, huh?

209
00:25:04,937 --> 00:25:07,187
-l would.
-What do you want, Stryker?

210
00:25:09,675 --> 00:25:11,784
Bradley was killed three days ago.

211
00:25:13,145 --> 00:25:14,575
Wade before that.

212
00:25:15,547 --> 00:25:18,447
I believe that someone is hunting down
our old team.

213
00:25:19,818 --> 00:25:23,328
-Anyone else?
-As far as I know, Victor is safe.

214
00:25:25,657 --> 00:25:28,057
But whoever it is has names, addresses.

215
00:25:28,494 --> 00:25:30,274
I can take care of myself.

216
00:25:32,498 --> 00:25:34,458
This is not about you, Logan.

217
00:25:38,237 --> 00:25:39,907
Your country needs you.

218
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:42,495
I'm Canadian.

219
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:46,139
I know you, Logan! I know who you are!

220
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:03,519
-Miss Kayla, Miss Kayla, look what I did.
-What did you do?

221
00:26:15,374 --> 00:26:17,244
Bye, Miss Silverfox! Bye!

222
00:26:24,450 --> 00:26:25,740
What's wrong?

223
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,990
Stryker came by today.

224
00:26:31,356 --> 00:26:32,616
Don't worry. I said no.

225
00:26:32,891 --> 00:26:35,521
Why is he bothering you
after all these years?

226
00:26:35,994 --> 00:26:38,014
Because I'm the best there is at what I do,

227
00:26:38,397 --> 00:26:39,827
but what I do best isn't very nice.

228
00:26:40,132 --> 00:26:43,352
You're not an animal, Logan.
What you have is a gift.

229
00:26:43,902 --> 00:26:46,392
A gift. You can return a gift.

230
00:27:00,052 --> 00:27:01,421
Come on, fellas.

231
00:27:02,855 --> 00:27:04,085
All right.

232
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,190
Stay in the car.

233
00:27:06,992 --> 00:27:08,831
I'm just gonna ask nicely.

234
00:27:13,132 --> 00:27:14,882
You mind letting us go by?

235
00:27:15,868 --> 00:27:17,268
-You in some kind of a hurry there, pal?
-Hey, hey, hey.

236
00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:18,678
Are you?

237
00:27:18,937 --> 00:27:20,016
Just move your truck so we can go by.

238
00:27:20,272 --> 00:27:22,141
We're trying to have
a conversation there, all right?

239
00:27:22,508 --> 00:27:24,408
You start something,
you'd better be ready to finish it.

240
00:27:24,776 --> 00:27:25,946
Listen...

241
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:28,791
Hey, guys, take it easy! Calm down.

242
00:27:33,719 --> 00:27:36,329
-Your boyfriend's got a big mouth.
-l know.

243
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:40,218
Big temper, too. So please let us pass.

244
00:27:45,364 --> 00:27:48,434
-Thank you.
-Come on, man, let's go.

245
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:51,247
How'd you do that?

246
00:27:51,937 --> 00:27:54,216
Female powers of persuasion. It's a gift.

247
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:57,600
Oh, I see.
Do you have those powers over me?

248
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:00,600
Well, you didn't stay in the car, did you?

249
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,883
Why is the moon so lonely?

250
00:28:21,567 --> 00:28:22,527
Why?

251
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:25,192
Because she used to have a lover.

252
00:28:25,571 --> 00:28:27,650
-You tell this to the kids?
-No.

253
00:28:29,074 --> 00:28:31,594
His name was Kuekuatsheu
and they lived in the Spirit World together.

254
00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:34,654
Oh, this is a true story? All right.

255
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:37,483
And every night they would
wander the skies together,

