I seem to remember that girl
when she was about 85 pounds, huh?

510
01:00:04,801 --> 01:00:07,201
Oh, that's funny.
You're still so funny, Logan.

511
01:00:07,637 --> 01:00:08,657
You know where Victor is?

512
01:00:10,607 --> 01:00:12,797
-No idea.
-What's the island, slim?

513
01:00:15,779 --> 01:00:17,419
Don't let the door hit you
on the way out, Logan.

514
01:00:17,747 --> 01:00:19,767
Listen, I ain't leaving here
till you tell me where Victor is.

515
01:00:20,150 --> 01:00:22,670
So come on, bub, for old times’ sake, huh?

516
01:00:24,421 --> 01:00:27,520
Did you just call me Blob?

517
01:00:29,826 --> 01:00:31,056
No, but...

518
01:00:37,267 --> 01:00:39,547
I told you not to mention his weight.
Why'd you call him Blob?

519
01:00:39,970 --> 01:00:42,080
I didn't call him Blob. I said “bub”.

520
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:44,402
-God damn it.
-Hey, hey, hey. Hey, Logan.

521
01:00:44,774 --> 01:00:45,854
I got an idea.

522
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:49,814
-This is your idea of an idea?
-I'm trying to help you out, Logan.

523
01:00:50,213 --> 01:00:51,583
Dukes don't like you that much
and you know it.

524
01:00:51,882 --> 01:00:53,842
-Yeah, the feeling's mutual.
-Well, use them gloves, man.

525
01:00:54,217 --> 01:00:57,937
Dance with him a little bit.
Allow him to let his anger out on you.

526
01:00:58,555 --> 01:01:01,185
Figure if you do that, he'll probably
tell you everything you want to know.

527
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:03,208
Come on, man, look at him.

528
01:01:03,527 --> 01:01:05,897
Got a big old ass coming out
the front of his shirt.

529
01:01:06,329 --> 01:01:08,409
Jesus. He's gonna have a coronary,
for Christ's sake.

530
01:01:08,798 --> 01:01:11,287
Is there even a stretcher big enough
to take this guy out of here?

531
01:01:13,470 --> 01:01:15,459
It ain't him I'm worried about
getting out of here ona stretcher.

532
01:01:15,839 --> 01:01:18,009
-You're an asshole.
-Come on, Logan.

533
01:01:20,544 --> 01:01:22,274
-Whup his ass!
-You want it?

534
01:01:22,612 --> 01:01:24,282
Dance with him, Fred!
Just like I taught you.

535
01:01:25,215 --> 01:01:26,085
You want to dance with me?

536
01:01:26,316 --> 01:01:28,745
-Come on, Fred!
-Oh! Oh, that feels good.

537
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:33,785
Hey! Guess what?

538
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:36,635
See, he gonna talk now.

539
01:01:36,893 --> 01:01:38,973
-You got him right where you want him.
-Whose side are you on, anyway?

540
01:01:39,362 --> 01:01:40,622
Come on!

541
01:01:41,464 --> 01:01:43,163
Come on, now, lamb chop!

542
01:01:59,015 --> 01:02:00,035
Damn!

543
01:02:14,831 --> 01:02:16,141
Now, where's Victor?

544
01:02:47,831 --> 01:02:50,441
Little dark for sunglasses, don't you think?

545
01:03:06,416 --> 01:03:10,196
-Please, don't! Please, don't!
-Victor!

546
01:03:14,357 --> 01:03:16,407
Hey, hey! Where's Victor?

547
01:03:18,261 --> 01:03:22,951
Yeah. Victor's with Stryker on the island.

548
01:03:23,700 --> 01:03:25,839
They run it together.

549
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:29,950
What? They what?
Victor will be with Stryker?

550
01:03:31,241 --> 01:03:32,231
Yeah.

551
01:03:33,143 --> 01:03:34,873
You didn't know that?

552
01:03:55,131 --> 01:03:59,000
All that's left now is Logan.
I trust you can handle that.

553
01:04:00,870 --> 01:04:04,180
-I did before, didn't 1?
-Oh, yes. You did that.

554
01:04:08,011 --> 01:04:10,881
Our deal. It still applies, right?

555
01:04:13,650 --> 01:04:16,370
Of course.
Now bag him and tag him, Captain.

556
01:04:25,762 --> 01:04:27,282
What's the island?

557
01:04:28,732 --> 01:04:31,952
It's where Stryker takes
them after Victor's caught them.

558
01:04:33,470 --> 01:04:35,459
Wait, hang on a minute. Takes who?

559
01:04:37,474 --> 01:04:38,614
Mutants.

560
01:04:39,609 --> 01:04:43,209
Rumor is that Stryker's doing
experiments on them there.

561
01:04:46,716 --> 01:04:48,705
I mean, you never wondered
what happened to them?

562
01:04:49,085 --> 01:04:50,605
I tried not to.

563
01:05:07,203 --> 01:05:10,192
They killed her so I'd let them
put Adamantium in me.

564
01:05:13,943 --> 01:05:16,403
They killed her for a goddamn experiment.

565
01:05:20,884 --> 01:05:24,604
-Where is it? Where is it?
-Logan, Stryker kept it real secret.

566
01:05:29,692 --> 01:05:33,202
But a prisoner escaped there once.

567
01:05:33,797 --> 01:05:35,937
-Who?
-His name was Remy LeBeau.

568
01:05:36,332 --> 01:05:38,292
He was a street hustler from New Orleans.

569
01:05:38,668 --> 01:05:41,158
The guards at the prison
called him Gambit

570
01:05:41,604 --> 01:05:42,774
because he kept taking
all their money at poker.

571
01:05:43,039 --> 01:05:44,739
-That's all I know.
-What's Stryker up to, Fred?

572
01:05:45,074 --> 01:05:46,594
What's the endgame?

573
01:05:48,845 --> 01:05:52,765
He's taking their powers.
Trying to combine them somehow.

574
01:05:53,416 --> 01:05:55,906
That's all l know, Logan. That's all Il know.

575
01:05:56,920 --> 01:06:00,110
If I have to come back here,
I'm gonna take your head off.

576
01:06:04,360 --> 01:06:06,230
I'm coming with you, Logan.

577
01:06:07,964 --> 01:06:10,364
-There's no redemption where I'm going.
-l ain't asking.

578
01:06:48,438 --> 01:06:49,928
There's our dude.

579
01:06:56,446 --> 01:06:57,935
That's cool.

580
01:06:58,248 --> 01:07:00,028
I'm gonna go cover the back
in case he rabbits.

581
01:07:00,383 --> 01:07:02,223
-I'm not gonna fight with him.
-Yeah, right.

582
01:07:02,585 --> 01:07:04,365
What? I get in fights with everybody?

583
01:07:04,721 --> 01:07:06,561
Don't dogs kill cats?

584
01:07:06,923 --> 01:07:09,062
Just go cover the back, will you?

585
01:07:13,396 --> 01:07:15,566
-Give me 500.
-I'm in.

586
01:07:21,804 --> 01:07:23,324
Are you Remy LeBeau?

587
01:07:25,742 --> 01:07:27,672
-Do l owe you money?
-No.

588
01:07:29,612 --> 01:07:31,252
Then Remy LeBeau I am.

589
01:07:50,133 --> 01:07:52,593
Large blind's 100. Small blind's 50.

590
01:07:53,903 --> 01:07:57,413
-May I deal you in?
-What can I get for 17 bucks?

591
01:07:59,008 --> 01:08:00,118
$17?

592
01:08:01,911 --> 01:08:03,661
A cab ride home, perhaps?

593
01:08:08,484 --> 01:08:10,824
You my brother's new babysitter, John?

594
01:08:12,021 --> 01:08:13,191
l ain't Bradley, Victor.

595
01:08:13,456 --> 01:08:15,266
And your creepy black coat
don't scare me.

596
01:08:15,625 --> 01:08:16,675
Really?

597
01:08:17,660 --> 01:08:19,300
Worked on Dukes.

598
01:08:19,629 --> 01:08:21,559
You shouldn't have done that,
‘cause now I'm gonna kill you

599
01:08:21,930 --> 01:08:23,770
before Logan even gets a chance.

600
01:08:24,367 --> 01:08:26,587
So what brings you to our fair city, sir?

601
01:08:27,002 --> 01:08:28,343
Victor Creed.

602
01:08:31,040 --> 01:08:32,500
And who's that?

603
01:08:33,443 --> 01:08:34,403
The man I'm gonna kill.

604
01:08:36,345 --> 01:08:39,245
He works with a man named Stryker
on an island.

605
01:08:41,184 --> 01:08:44,224
-Just need to know where it is.
-And why would you think I know that?

606
01:08:44,754 --> 01:08:47,243
Well, ‘cause I know who you are, Gambit.

607
01:08:48,725 --> 01:08:52,825
You're the guy who escaped and you're
the guy who's gonna take me back there.

608
01:08:54,497 --> 01:08:57,687
You know, John, there's something
l always wanted to tell you.

609
01:09:04,240 --> 01:09:06,870
You're predictable.

610
01:09:10,078 --> 01:09:12,249
I can feel your spine, Johnny Boy.

611
01:09:13,549 --> 01:09:15,919
That's funny. Never knew you had one.

612
01:09:19,889 --> 01:09:22,788
Those are mighty nice tags
you have on there, sir.

613
01:09:24,594 --> 01:09:27,283
The men who took me wore
tags just like them.

614
01:09:31,367 --> 01:09:33,417
Hey, now, bub, you listen to me.

615
01:09:51,354 --> 01:09:52,994
Damn it. That little...

616
01:10:07,070 --> 01:10:10,320
Two years I rotted in that hellhole
and I ain't never going back.

617
01:10:15,078 --> 01:10:16,218
Shiny.

618
01:10:19,082 --> 01:10:20,922
Tell me something, Jimmy.

619
01:10:21,884 --> 01:10:23,964
Do you even know how to kill me?

620
01:10:24,353 --> 01:10:26,723
I'm gonna cut your goddamned head off.

621
01:10:27,757 --> 01:10:29,366
See if that works.

622
01:10:39,235 --> 01:10:41,255
You're getting slow, old man.

623
01:10:50,279 --> 01:10:51,979
You son of a bitch.

624
01:10:55,885 --> 01:10:58,375
You're gonna die for what you did to her.

625
01:11:22,979 --> 01:11:24,059
Victor!

626
01:11:34,190 --> 01:11:36,000
Well, that's a nice stick.

627
01:12:34,750 --> 01:12:36,940
Okay, shithead, here's the deal.

628
01:12:37,353 --> 01:12:40,283
See, you're gonna take me to this island,
where I can kill Creed, Stryker

629
01:12:40,790 --> 01:12:44,450
and pretty much everyone you hate
in this world. Do you understand?

630
01:12:45,661 --> 01:12:47,091
You're really gonna kill them?

631
01:12:47,396 --> 01:12:49,826
As long as you stay out of my way, yeah.

632
01:13:04,247 --> 01:13:05,507
Colonel?

633
01:13:06,282 --> 01:13:08,212
-General?
-Is this Weapon XI?

634
01:13:11,087 --> 01:13:13,607
All their strengths
and none of their weaknesses.

635
01:13:14,056 --> 01:13:15,726
You really hate them, don't you?

636
01:13:16,058 --> 01:13:17,698
No, I don't hate them.

637
01:13:18,361 --> 01:13:22,081
After 20 years of working with mutants,
I just know what they can do.

638
01:13:26,535 --> 01:13:30,075
We can win this war before it starts
and save countless lives in the process.

639
01:13:30,673 --> 01:13:33,773
Pre-emptive action is
the only action here, General.

640
01:13:34,310 --> 01:13:37,560
The days of our country
sitting on the sidelines are over.

641
01:13:39,015 --> 01:13:42,555
We need to take the fight to the enemy
before they take the fight to us.

642
01:13:43,152 --> 01:13:45,612
-l admire your passion, I do.
-Thank you.

643
01:13:46,756 --> 01:13:48,746
But this is as far as it goes.

644
01:13:50,059 --> 01:13:53,159
-Weapon X was a hiccup.
-We know about your son, Bill.

645
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:57,363
We know he's a mutant,
and we know he killed your wife.

646
01:13:57,900 --> 01:14:00,559
-You shouldn't have kept that from us.
-That...

647
01:14:02,505 --> 01:14:03,995
That has nothing
to do with my work, General.

648
01:14:04,307 --> 01:14:05,447
Bullshit.

649
01:14:05,942 --> 01:14:08,812
You're too close to this.
I'm shutting you down.

650
01:14:09,979 --> 01:14:13,849
Okay. You're right. I won't lie to you.

651
01:14:17,887 --> 01:14:21,076
My son did bring
the problem home for me,

652
01:14:23,059 --> 01:14:24,579
but I took an oath

653
01:14:26,329 --> 01:14:28,289
to protect the American people

654
01:14:29,699 --> 01:14:32,279
from every threat, both foreign

655
01:14:40,776 --> 01:14:42,206
and domestic.

656
01:14:50,386 --> 01:14:51,966
-You don't like flying, huh?
-I'm fine.

657
01:14:52,288 --> 01:14:53,517
-Just concentrate on what you're doing.
-You sure?

658
01:14:53,789 --> 01:14:55,188
You got a bit of sweat
on your brow there.

659
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:56,921
Very funny. Just keep your eyes on the...

660
01:14:57,226 --> 01:14:58,746
On the what? The clouds?
Keep my eyes on the clouds?

661
01:14:59,061 --> 01:15:00,431
You're up and down
like a freaking yo-yo here!

662
01:15:00,730 --> 01:15:02,809
-Where'd you get this thing, anyway?
-Oh, this is my baby.

663
01:15:03,199 --> 01:15:05,568
I won her in a game. Jacks over fives.

664
01:15:07,236 --> 01:15:08,316
Great.

665
01:15:09,071 --> 01:15:10,941
Relax. We're almost there.

666
01:15:14,610 --> 01:15:17,599
There it is. The island. Three Mile Island.

667
01:15:18,581 --> 01:15:20,281
Hiding in plain sight.

668
01:15:23,085 --> 01:15:25,695
No one's gonna snoop
around a nuclear reactor.

669
01:15:26,155 --> 01:15:27,884
They think it's gonna turn them
into freaks.

670
01:15:28,224 --> 01:15:30,004
-Like you?
-Right.

671
01:15:33,029 --> 01:15:35,399
All right. You ready?
Because it's now or never. Let's go.

672
01:15:35,831 --> 01:15:37,061
About time.

673
01:15:46,475 --> 01:15:49,575
Hey, if it makes you feel any better,
this is really gonna hurt.

674
01:15:50,112 --> 01:15:52,542
Well, yeah, it kind of does, actually.

675
01:15:54,116 --> 01:15:56,636
-Good luck.
-Likewise.

676
01:15:59,288 --> 01:16:00,308
Oh, shit.

677
01:16:07,930 --> 01:16:10,120
How you doing? Everything all right?

678
01:16:12,001 --> 01:16:14,191
-Is he ready yet?
-A few more hours.

679
01:16:14,603 --> 01:16:17,413
-And he will respond to my commands?
-Absolutely.

680
01:17:21,537 --> 01:17:22,587
Logan.

681
01:17:24,039 --> 01:17:25,849
Welcome back to the war.

682
01:17:27,143 --> 01:17:29,633
Before I gut you, I want to know why.

683
01:17:31,714 --> 01:17:33,734
I needed your powers for the Pool.

684
01:17:34,116 --> 01:17:36,256
-For the what?
-The mutant killer.

685
01:17:37,520 --> 01:17:38,890
Deadpool.

686
01:17:40,356 --> 01:17:42,056
Years of searching and refining,

687
01:17:42,391 --> 01:17:45,851
finding the right powers
that can coexist in one body

688
01:17:46,428 --> 01:17:48,298
without ripping it apart.

689
01:17:49,765 --> 01:17:52,165
My son was the first piece of the puzzle.

690
01:17:54,370 --> 01:17:56,240
Logan, you were the last.

691
01:17:56,605 --> 01:17:58,535
You made Weapon XI possible.

692
01:17:59,875 --> 01:18:04,445
l asked you to help,
but you said you wanted the quiet life.

693
01:18:07,216 --> 01:18:08,236
Well,

694
01:18:09,118 --> 01:18:13,368
I've learned that nothing motivates
the men in your family like revenge.

695
01:18:31,574 --> 01:18:32,803
Who are you?

696
01:18:33,876 --> 01:18:35,746
Oh, she's real, old friend.

697
01:18:47,957 --> 01:18:50,767
Did you really think
we'd just let you walk away?

698
01:18:51,460 --> 01:18:53,270
You're a dangerous man.

699
01:18:53,629 --> 01:18:56,029
We like to keep an eye on dangerous men.

700
01:18:57,132 --> 01:18:59,212
Tell him about the day you died.

701
01:19:05,407 --> 01:19:08,097
They gave me a shot
of hydrochlorothiazide.

702
01:19:10,579 --> 01:19:13,768
It reduces the heart rate so low
it appears you flatlined.

703
01:19:26,161 --> 01:19:27,911
Don't be angry with her.

704
01:19:29,198 --> 01:19:31,568
She's a real credit to your species.

705
01:19:35,237 --> 01:19:38,257
Did you know that her sister has
diamond-hard skin?

706
01:19:39,541 --> 01:19:41,851
Kayla's mutation is tactohypnosis.

707
01:19:42,845 --> 01:19:45,505
She can influence people
as long as she touches them.

708
01:19:45,981 --> 01:19:48,260
Quite a useful tool in a seduction.

709
01:19:48,684 --> 01:19:50,704
It was never real, my friend.

710
01:19:56,425 --> 01:19:58,065
It was real for me.

711
01:20:00,329 --> 01:20:04,228
I told you if you came down this road,
you wouldn't like what you found.

712
01:20:11,040 --> 01:20:15,230
That story you told me about a man
who gets flowers for the moon,

713
01:20:17,913 --> 01:20:19,492
l had it backwards.

714
01:20:22,951 --> 01:20:25,971
I thought you were the moon
and I was your wolverine.

715
01:20:28,724 --> 01:20:31,064
But you're the trickster, aren't you?

716
01:20:32,061 --> 01:20:34,170
I'm just the fool who got played.

717
01:20:36,532 --> 01:20:39,142
The worst part of it is,
I should have known.

718
01:20:42,638 --> 01:20:44,568
But l ignored my instincts.

719
01:20:48,510 --> 01:20:50,440
lignored what I really am.

720
01:20:55,351 --> 01:20:57,521
But that won't ever happen again.

721
01:21:29,551 --> 01:21:31,221
-Colonel?
-Not now, Kayla.

722
01:21:31,553 --> 01:21:33,742
I've done everything you've asked.

723
01:21:35,557 --> 01:21:36,786
My sister.

724
01:21:37,960 --> 01:21:40,590
You said if 1 helped you, you'd let her go.

725
01:21:41,063 --> 01:21:45,103
Kayla, it's not as simple as that.
Her mutation is unique. Quite beautiful.

726
01:21:45,768 --> 01:21:47,698
We just need a little more time
to analyze it, that's all.

727
01:21:48,070 --> 01:21:49,469
You let him go?

728
01:21:53,175 --> 01:21:55,225
-Victor, please.
-You can't let him go.

729
01:21:55,611 --> 01:21:57,340
-You can't beat him, Victor.
-Then give me the Adamantium!

730
01:21:57,679 --> 01:21:58,879
-Your tests came back.
-We had a deal!

731
01:21:59,148 --> 01:22:01,458
You would never survive the operation.

732
01:22:03,986 --> 01:22:06,736
-l can take anything he can.
-No, you can't.

733
01:22:07,956 --> 01:22:11,416
You're my favorite soldier, Victor.
Be patient. Your time will come.

734
01:22:11,994 --> 01:22:13,393
He's using us.

735
01:22:22,204 --> 01:22:25,224
How about this time you die for real?

736
01:22:27,276 --> 01:22:28,505
Let me go.

737
01:22:31,313 --> 01:22:33,533
Your little mind games don't work on me.

738
01:22:33,949 --> 01:22:35,089
Victor!

739
01:23:09,618 --> 01:23:11,428
Feels good, doesn't it?

740
01:23:12,955 --> 01:23:14,415
All that rage.

741
01:23:16,391 --> 01:23:18,821
-Do it.
-Logan!

742
01:23:20,529 --> 01:23:23,719
-You're not an animal.
-Oh, yes, you are.

743
01:23:28,270 --> 01:23:29,500
Do it.

744
01:23:33,542 --> 01:23:34,802
Finish it.

745
01:23:59,535 --> 01:24:00,675
Logan?

746
01:24:04,206 --> 01:24:07,546
My sister. They have my sister.

747
01:24:08,544 --> 01:24:11,094
Please. I didn't trick you into loving me.

748
01:24:12,281 --> 01:24:14,121
It was real for me, too.

749
01:24:16,985 --> 01:24:20,005
Please, I'm so sorry. They have my sister.

750
01:24:22,024 --> 01:24:23,284
Where is she?

751
01:24:28,964 --> 01:24:31,154
-Activate Weapon XI!
-The bonding process isn't complete.

752
01:24:31,567 --> 01:24:32,967
Just do it! Now!

753
01:25:36,431 --> 01:25:37,920
Come on. Come on!

754
01:26:29,518 --> 01:26:30,478
Okay.

755
01:26:31,687 --> 01:26:32,797
Perfect.

756
01:26:33,055 --> 01:26:34,605
-Kayla, get these kids out of here.
-Logan...

757
01:26:34,923 --> 01:26:36,532
Find another way out.

758
01:26:37,292 --> 01:26:39,132
Okay. Let's go.

759
01:26:40,028 --> 01:26:41,608
Wade, is that you?

760
01:26:45,634 --> 01:26:48,594
Guess Stryker finally figured out
how to shut you up.

761
01:26:51,139 --> 01:26:52,219
Now...

762
01:26:59,648 --> 01:27:00,698
Wade?

763
01:27:01,950 --> 01:27:03,730
You don't have to do this.

764
01:27:04,886 --> 01:27:06,616
All right, maybe you do.

765
01:27:13,829 --> 01:27:15,499
You're shitting me.

766
01:27:21,002 --> 01:27:22,552
Shoot on sight!

767
01:27:30,679 --> 01:27:33,429
-I can help! Point me at them!
-Go.

768
01:27:41,790 --> 01:27:43,130
Go! Now!

769
01:27:49,664 --> 01:27:51,834
-Did I get them?
-Yeah.

770
01:28:02,344 --> 01:28:03,654
-Let's go.
-I can't go.

771
01:28:03,945 --> 01:28:06,224
-Kayla, come on!
-l have to stay here.

772
01:28:07,082 --> 01:28:08,482
You take them.

773
01:28:09,684 --> 01:28:11,584
Go! Go!

774
01:28:39,748 --> 01:28:40,977
Go left.

775
01:28:41,249 --> 01:28:42,269
Left.

776
01:28:43,285 --> 01:28:44,775
-What?
-We go left.

777
01:28:45,086 --> 01:28:46,896
-You can't see.
-Trust me.

778
01:29:01,803 --> 01:29:03,883
Let's see you dance up here.

779
01:29:40,742 --> 01:29:42,492
Nobody kills you but me.

780
01:29:51,553 --> 01:29:52,923
Back to back!

781
01:29:54,890 --> 01:29:57,030
-I got him!
-Oh, no, you don't.

782
01:31:30,618 --> 01:31:32,578
Stop! This can't be the way.

783
01:31:32,954 --> 01:31:34,244
-This is the way.
-How do you know?

784
01:31:34,522 --> 01:31:36,102
I just know. Come on.

785
01:31:47,769 --> 01:31:49,319
Adamantium bullets.

786
01:31:50,205 --> 01:31:52,955
Let's see him heal with
a few of these through his thick skull.

787
01:31:53,441 --> 01:31:55,661
You can't stop him, even with that.

788
01:31:56,378 --> 01:31:58,487
-He'll heal.
-His brain may heal,

789
01:32:00,882 --> 01:32:02,991
but his memories won't grow back.

790
01:32:19,901 --> 01:32:22,741
This doesn't change anything
between us, Victor.

791
01:32:24,439 --> 01:32:27,129
-We're done.
-We can never be done, Jimmy.

792
01:32:28,843 --> 01:32:32,003
We're brothers,
and brothers look out for each other.

793
01:33:06,481 --> 01:33:08,231
-You miss me?
-Ah, Jesus.

794
01:33:09,984 --> 01:33:12,064
You know, when you said
you were gonna kill everyone,

795
01:33:12,454 --> 01:33:14,624
I thought you may
just have been exaggerating.

796
01:33:15,023 --> 01:33:16,253
Yeah.

797
01:33:17,525 --> 01:33:19,365
Do I look like a man who exaggerates?

798
01:33:19,727 --> 01:33:21,456
-You're welcome.
-Logan?

799
01:33:24,199 --> 01:33:25,308
Logan.

800
01:33:29,437 --> 01:33:31,577
There's kids trying to get off the island.
Split up. Go!

801
01:33:31,973 --> 01:33:33,202
I'm on it.

802
01:33:41,349 --> 01:33:43,159
Kayla! Kayla!

803
01:33:47,522 --> 01:33:48,512
Hey.

804
01:33:53,695 --> 01:33:54,955
I love you.

805
01:34:07,542 --> 01:34:09,002
-Hey...
-I'm so cold.

806
01:34:09,310 --> 01:34:11,940
Listen to me.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

807
01:34:12,413 --> 01:34:13,702
Understand?

808
01:34:13,982 --> 01:34:16,822
Just go easy. Nice and easy. That's it.
That's it.

809
01:34:19,654 --> 01:34:21,844
Okay. I'm gonna get you help.

810
01:34:45,580 --> 01:34:46,809
Logan!

811
01:35:43,371 --> 01:35:45,591
I should make you pull the trigger.

812
01:35:46,674 --> 01:35:49,254
But that would make us
no better than you.

813
01:35:50,712 --> 01:35:52,292
Throw the gun away.

814
01:35:55,783 --> 01:35:57,013
Turn around.

815
01:35:57,819 --> 01:36:01,859
Walk until your feet bleed.
And then keep walking.

816
01:36:40,495 --> 01:36:42,075
ft will be all right, Scott.

817
01:36:42,397 --> 01:36:44,797
My name is Charles Xavier.

818
01:36:45,233 --> 01:36:46,983
I'm a mutant like you.

819
01:36:47,335 --> 01:36:50,995
-l can hear your thoughts.
-Yes, and can hear yours.

820
01:36:52,373 --> 01:36:55,772
You're safe now. Come. We have to go.

821
01:36:57,278 --> 01:36:58,918
Come on, let's go.

822
01:37:45,460 --> 01:37:46,920
The kids are safe.

823
01:37:52,500 --> 01:37:53,580
Damn.

824
01:37:57,171 --> 01:37:59,801
-Who are you?
-What do you mean, who am I?

825
01:38:00,274 --> 01:38:03,174
I'm the guy who brought you here.
Now, we got to go.

826
01:38:04,345 --> 01:38:05,925
Where the hell am I?

827
01:38:06,247 --> 01:38:08,147
Listen to me. I'm a friend.

828
01:38:08,883 --> 01:38:11,223
-I'm a friend.
-Yeah? What's my name?

829
01:38:11,652 --> 01:38:14,282
-What's my name?
-Your name is Logan.

830
01:38:19,026 --> 01:38:21,306
You need to trust me. We have to go.

831
01:38:27,101 --> 01:38:28,330
Follow me.

832
01:38:34,041 --> 01:38:35,091
Now!

833
01:39:08,976 --> 01:39:10,375
Do you know her?

834
01:39:14,515 --> 01:39:15,655
No.

835
01:39:20,521 --> 01:39:22,361
Hey, these boys aren't gonna like
what you've done to this place.

836
01:39:22,723 --> 01:39:24,393
We really need to go.

837
01:39:25,326 --> 01:39:26,936
I'll find my own way.

838
01:39:32,133 --> 01:39:33,362
Good luck.

839
01:41:04,759 --> 01:41:06,159
Colonel Stryker?

840
01:41:10,698 --> 01:41:13,858
-Colonel William Stryker?
-Yes.

841
01:41:15,536 --> 01:41:17,236
You're wanted for questioning
in connection with the death

842
01:41:17,572 --> 01:41:19,742
of General Munson, sir.

843
01:46:56,543 --> 01:46:57,413
Another.

844
01:47:00,614 --> 01:47:01,603
You're American?

845
01:47:03,317 --> 01:47:04,777
Canadian, I think.

846
01:47:06,186 --> 01:47:07,795
Are you drinking to forget?

847
01:47:10,357 --> 01:47:13,927
No, I'm drinking to remember.

